That's why I love this group!
To answer your questions, no, my trailing arms, which I somehow
mistakenly call swing arms, do not seem to bent in any way. The rubber
on the bottom of the stops is where it is worn off, I can't possbly
guess how the rubber on the top of the stops could ever get worn off in
a lowered condition unless your suspension drops down repeatedly instead
of being forced up. And yes, I checked my manual pictures agaisnt my
front end and it looks stock. I have seen pictures in Hot VW of the
lowering adjusters and I don't have that stuff welded on my torsion bar
tubes. Ands as far as the snap, crackle and pop goes, quit cheering me
up ! I think I hear that kind of thing going on on my passenger side.
For the last month or so I have heard odd thunking noise from that side
and now have attributed it to your e-mail descriptions, thanks for
making me feel safer !

