Does your front end have the lowering adjusting parts welded in the
center of
the front beam?  If so you need to jack up your bus and install jack
stands.

Then adjust the front suspension so the wheels end up as far down as
possible.
  If the DPO removed some of the spring leaves the remaining leaves
could be

snap, crackle, popping and ready to let the trailing arms to pop out of
the
front end while you are driving!  If sprong leaves are missing then you
need

to remove them and install new ones.   Eric&Barb

